## Exception Type Refactor Plan

### Goal
- Replace generic `throw new Exception(...)` in service code with the most appropriate built-in .NET exception type.
- Add custom application exceptions only when built-in .NET exceptions do not express the case clearly enough.
- Update API exception handling so these exception types produce the intended HTTP status codes.

### 1. AuthService Exception Mapping

#### [MODIFY] [AuthService.cs](file:///d:/Class/SU26/PRN232/CODE/MangaManagementSystem/MangaManagementSystem.Business/Services/Implements/AuthService.cs)
- Replace duplicate email/username failure with `InvalidOperationException`.
- Replace missing role failure with `KeyNotFoundException`.
- Replace invalid login credentials with `UnauthorizedAccessException`.
- Replace inactive/locked account failures with `UnauthorizedAccessException`.
- Replace invalid/expired refresh token failure with `UnauthorizedAccessException`.
- Replace missing user failures with `KeyNotFoundException`.
- Replace wrong current password failure with `UnauthorizedAccessException`.
- Keep exception messages unchanged.
- Do not change repository usage, AutoMapper mapping, password hashing, token generation, refresh token rotation, or response DTOs.

### 2. Exception Middleware Mapping

#### [MODIFY] [ExceptionMiddleware.cs](file:///d:/Class/SU26/PRN232/CODE/MangaManagementSystem/MangaManagementSystem.WebApi/Middleware/ExceptionMiddleware.cs)
- Keep `ArgumentException` mapped to HTTP 400 Bad Request.
- Keep `KeyNotFoundException` mapped to HTTP 404 Not Found.
- Add `UnauthorizedAccessException` mapped to HTTP 401 Unauthorized.
- Add `InvalidOperationException` mapped to HTTP 409 Conflict.
- Keep all unknown exceptions mapped to HTTP 500 Internal Server Error.

### 3. Custom Exception Rule
- Do not add custom exceptions for the current auth service because built-in .NET exception types are expressive enough.
- If future cases need custom exceptions, place them under `MangaManagementSystem.Business/Exceptions`.
- Middleware must map any new custom exception type explicitly.

